How to Contribute
Fork the Repository: Click the "Fork" button at the top-right of this page.
Clone Your Fork: Clone your forked repository to your local machine.
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your_username/Percival-Pi.git
Create a Branch: Create a new branch for your feature or bugfix.
bash
Copy code
git checkout -b feature-name
Make Changes: Add your changes to the code.
Commit and Push: Commit your changes and push to your fork.
bash
Copy code
git add .
git commit -m "Description of changes"
git push origin feature-name
Create a Pull Request: Open a pull request to merge your changes into the main repository.
